Title: 1481. The Time Traveler's Wife
Description: Henry DeTamble, a librarian, possesses a unique gene that lets him involuntarily travel through time. His wife, Claire Abshire, finds it difficult to cope with it.

Title: 1482. Tango & Cash
Description: Framed by their ruthless arch-nemesis, a pair of mismatched LAPD officers must put their differences aside to get even with the brutal crime baron who sent them to rot in a maximum-security prison.

Title: 1483. She's All That
Description: When Zack's famous girlfriend, Taylor, cheats on him with another boy and parts ways with him, he makes a bet with his friends to turn a socially inept Laney into their high school's next prom queen.

Title: 1484. Madea's Family Reunion
Description: While planning her family reunion, a pistol-packing grandma must contend with other dramas, including her love-troubled nieces and the runaway who was placed in her care.

Title: 1485. Bewitched
Description: Thinking he can overshadow an unknown actress in the part, an egocentric actor unknowingly gets a witch cast in an upcoming television remake of the classic sitcom Bewitched (1964).

Title: 1486. Saw IV
Description: Despite Jigsaw's death, and in order to save the lives of two of his colleagues, Lieutenant Rigg is forced to take part in a new game, which promises to test him to the limit.

Title: 1487. The Boss
Description: A titan of industry is sent to prison after she's caught insider trading. When she emerges ready to rebrand herself as America's latest sweetheart, not everyone she screwed over is so quick to forgive and forget.

Title: 1488. Dave
Description: An uncanny Presidential lookalike named Dave is recruited by the Secret Service to become a momentary stand-in for the President of the United States.

Title: 1489. The Holiday
Description: Amanda lives in LA and is a movie trailer editor. Iris lives in Surrey and is a journalist. The two decide to swap houses for two weeks at Christmas - both trying to forget their troubled love lives, until love finds them anyways.

Title: 1490. Rising Sun
Description: When an escort girl is found dead in the offices of a Japanese company in Los Angeles, detectives Web Smith and John Connor act as liaison between the company's executives and the investigating cop Tom Graham.

Title: 1491. Forgetting Sarah Marshall
Description: Devastated Peter takes a Hawaiian vacation in order to deal with the recent break-up with his TV star girlfriend, Sarah. Little does he know, Sarah's traveling to the same resort as her ex - and she's bringing along her new boyfriend.

Title: 1492. The Sorcerer's Apprentice
Description: A protege of the magician Merlin must train his teacher's successor - an introverted but resourceful physics prodigy - in the art of sorcery to prevent the return of Morgana le Fay.

Title: 1493. Beavis and Butt-Head Do America
Description: Our intrepid adolescent heroes wake up to find their beloved television stolen, and embark on an epic journey across America to recover it, and, who knows, maybe even score.

Title: 1494. Scent of a Woman
Description: A prep school student needing money agrees to "babysit" a blind man, but the job is not at all what he anticipated.

Title: 1495. A Nightmare on Elm Street
Description: The spectre of a disfigured man haunts the children of the parents who murdered him, stalking and killing them in their dreams.

Title: 1496. The Last Song
Description: A rebellious girl is sent to a Southern beach town for the summer to stay with her father. Through their mutual love of music, the estranged duo learn to reconnect.

Title: 1497. Jarhead
Description: A psychological study of Marine's state of mind during the Gulf War. Told through the eyes of a U.S. Marine sniper who struggles to cope with boredom, a sense of isolation, and other issues back home.

Title: 1498. Black Mass
Description: The true story of Whitey Bulger, the brother of a state senator and the most infamous violent criminal in the history of South Boston, who became an FBI informant to take down a Mafia family invading his turf.

Title: 1499. The Crying Game
Description: A British soldier kidnapped by the IRA soon befriends one of his captors, who then becomes drawn into the soldier's world.

Title: 1500. Black Phone 2
Description: As Finn, now 17, struggles with life after his captivity, his sister begins receiving calls in her dreams from the black phone and seeing disturbing visions of three boys being stalked at a winter camp known as Alpine Lake.

Title: 1501. London Has Fallen
Description: Whilst in London, England for the British Prime Minister's funeral, Mike Banning is caught up in a terrorist plot to assassinate all the attending world leaders in one strike.

Title: 1502. The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift
Description: A teenager becomes a major competitor in the world of drift racing after moving in with his father in Tokyo to avoid a jail sentence in America.

Title: 1503. The Adjustment Bureau
Description: The relationship between a politician and a contemporary dancer is affected by mysterious forces keeping them apart.

Title: 1504. A Fish Called Wanda
Description: In London, four very different people team up on a jewel heist, then try to double-cross one another for the loot, complicated by their efforts to fool the very proper barrister Archibald Leach.

Title: 1505. Spy Game
Description: Retiring CIA agent Nathan Muir recalls his training of Tom Bishop while working against agency politics to free him from his Chinese captors.

Title: 1506. The Call of the Wild
Description: A sled dog struggles for survival in the wilds of the Yukon.

Title: 1507. Underworld: Awakening
Description: When human forces discover the existence of the Vampire and Lycan clans, a war to eradicate both species commences. The vampire warrior Selene leads the battle against humankind.

Title: 1508. Underworld: Evolution
Description: Picking up directly from the previous movie, vampire warrior Selene and the half werewolf Michael hunt for clues to reveal the history of their races and the war between them.

Title: 1509. Terminator: Dark Fate
Description: An augmented human and Sarah Connor must stop an advanced liquid Terminator from hunting down a young girl, whose fate is critical to the human race.

Title: 1510. Down and Out in Beverly Hills
Description: A rich but troubled family find their lives altered by the arrival of a vagrant who tries to drown himself in their swimming pool.

Title: 1511. The Wolfman
Description: Upon his return to his ancestral homeland, an American man is bitten and subsequently cursed by a werewolf.

Title: 1512. Mousehunt
Description: Two stumblebum inheritors are determined to rid their antique house of a mouse who is equally determined to stay where he is.

Title: 1513. The Electric Horseman
Description: A rodeo star past his prime steals his company's horse and rides into the desert, accompanied by a feisty reporter.

Title: 1514. Dog
Description: Two hard-charging former Army Rangers paired against their will, Briggs and a Belgian Malinois named Lulu, race down the Pacific Coast in hopes of making it to a fellow soldier's funeral on time.

Title: 1515. Patton
Description: The World War II phase of the career of controversial American general George S. Patton.

Title: 1516. Ender's Game
Description: Young Ender Wiggin is recruited by the International Military to lead the fight against the Formics, an insectoid alien race who had previously tried to invade Earth and had inflicted heavy losses on humankind.

Title: 1517. Miracles from Heaven
Description: Based on the incredible true story of the Beam family.

Title: 1518. A Beautiful Day in the Neighborhood
Description: Lloyd Vogel, a cynical journalist, gets acquainted with a kind-hearted television host Fred Rogers while writing an article on him. With time, they strike an unlikely friendship.

Title: 1519. Cinderella Man
Description: The true story of James J. Braddock, a supposedly washed-up boxer, who returned to the spotlight to win the heavyweight championship of the world.

Title: 1520. Onward
Description: Teenage elf brothers Ian and Barley embark on a magical quest to spend one more day with their late father. Like any good adventure, their journey is filled with cryptic maps, impossible obstacles and unimaginable discoveries.

Title: 1521. Napoleon
Description: An epic that details the chequered rise and fall of French Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte and his relentless journey to power through the prism of his addictive, volatile relationship with his wife, Josephine.

Title: 1522. Flatliners
Description: Five medical students experiment with "near death" experiences, until the dark consequences of past tragedies begin to jeopardize their lives.

Title: 1523. Deepwater Horizon
Description: A dramatization of the disaster in April 2010, when the offshore drilling rig called the Deepwater Horizon exploded, resulting in the worst oil spill in history.

Title: 1524. National Lampoon's Vacation
Description: The Griswold family's cross-country drive in their brand new Wagon Family Truckster to the Walley World theme park in California proves to be much more arduous than they ever anticipated.

Title: 1525. The Saint
Description: Simon "The Saint" Templar (Val Kilmer) is a thief for hire whose latest job to steal the secret process for cold fusion puts him at odds with a traitor bent on toppling the Russian government, as well as the woman who holds its secret.

Title: 1526. Stomp the Yard
Description: When his brother is murdered, a street dancer moves to Georgia to work his way through college. He joins a fraternity's step dancing team for a competition. Will he also get an education and the girl?

Title: 1527. Rules of Engagement
Description: An attorney defends an officer on trial for ordering his troops to fire on civilians after they stormed a U.S. embassy in a Middle Eastern country.

Title: 1528. The Cell
Description: An F.B.I. Agent persuades a social worker, who is adept with a new experimental technology, to enter the mind of a comatose serial killer in order to learn where he has hidden his latest kidnap victim.

Title: 1529. Misery
Description: After a famous author is rescued from a car crash by a fan of his novels, he comes to realize that the care he is receiving is only the beginning of a nightmare of captivity and abuse.

Title: 1530. Abominable
Description: Three teenagers must help a Yeti return to his family while avoiding a wealthy man and a zoologist who want him for their own needs.

Title: 1531. Friday Night Lights
Description: Based on H.G. Bissinger's book, which profiled the economically depressed town of Odessa, Texas and their heroic high school football team, The Permian High Panthers.

Title: 1532. Candyman
Description: A sequel to the horror film Candyman (1992) that returns to the now-gentrified Chicago neighborhood where the legend began.

Title: 1533. The Shaggy Dog
Description: A man tries to live a normal life despite the fact that he sometimes turns into a sheepdog.

Title: 1534. Prisoners
Description: A desperate father takes the law into his own hands after police fail to find two kidnapped girls.

Title: 1535. Get Him to the Greek
Description: A record company intern is hired to accompany out-of-control British rock star Aldous Snow to a concert at L.A.'s Greek Theater.

Title: 1536. The Devil's Advocate
Description: An exceptionally adept Florida lawyer is offered a job at a high-end New York City law firm with a high-end boss - the biggest opportunity of his career to date.

Title: 1537. The Omen
Description: Mysterious deaths surround an American ambassador. Could the child that he is raising actually be the Antichrist? The Devil's own son?

Title: 1538. Mission to Mars
Description: When the first manned mission to Mars meets with a catastrophic and mysterious disaster after reporting an unidentified structure, a rescue mission is launched to investigate the tragedy and bring back any survivors.

Title: 1539. Harlem Nights
Description: During the 1930s, a New York City illegal gambling house owner and his associates must deal with strong competition, gangsters, and corrupt cops in order to stay in business.

Title: 1540. Coyote Ugly
Description: Aspiring songwriter Violet Sanford, after getting a job at a women-run NYC bar that teases its male patrons, comes out of her shell.

Title: 1541. God's Not Dead
Description: College philosophy professor Mr. Radisson's curriculum is challenged by his new student, Josh, who believes God exists.

Title: 1542. Poseidon
Description: On New Year's Eve, the luxury ocean liner Poseidon capsizes after being swamped by a rogue wave. The survivors are left to fight for their lives as they attempt to escape the sinking ship.

Title: 1543. Fantasia 2000
Description: An update of the original film with new interpretations of great works of classical music.

Title: 1544. Three Kings
Description: In the aftermath of the Persian Gulf War, four soldiers set out to steal gold that was stolen from Kuwait, but they discover people who desperately need their help.

Title: 1545. The Color Purple
Description: A woman faces many hardships in her life, but ultimately finds extraordinary strength and hope in the unbreakable bonds of sisterhood.

Title: 1546. Jingle All the Way
Description: A father vows to get his son a Turbo Man action figure for Christmas. However, every store is sold out, and he must travel all over town and compete with everybody else in order to find one.

Title: 1547. Kiss the Girls
Description: Police hunting for a serial kidnapper are helped when a victim manages to escape for the first time.

Title: 1548. After Earth
Description: A crash landing leaves Kitai Raige and his father Cypher stranded on Earth, a millennium after events forced humanity's escape. With Cypher injured, Kitai must embark on a perilous journey to signal for help.

Title: 1549. Baby Mama
Description: A successful, single businesswoman who dreams of having a baby discovers she is infertile and hires a working class woman to be her unlikely surrogate.

Title: 1550. 2001: A Space Odyssey
Description: When a mysterious artifact is uncovered on the Moon, a spacecraft manned by two humans and one supercomputer is sent to Jupiter to find its origins.

Title: 1551. Dora and the Lost City of Gold
Description: Teenage explorer Dora leads her friends on an adventure to save her parents and solve the mystery behind a lost city of gold.

Title: 1552. Shanghai Knights
Description: When a Chinese rebel murders Chon's estranged father and escapes to England, Chon and Roy make their way to London with revenge on their minds.

Title: 1553. The Lucky One
Description: A Marine travels to Louisiana after serving three tours in Iraq and searches for the unknown woman he believes was his good luck charm during the war.

Title: 1554. The Wedding Planner
Description: Mary Fiore is San Francisco's most successful supplier of romance and glamor. She knows all the tricks. She knows all the rules. But then she breaks the most important rule of all: she falls in love with the groom.

Title: 1555. Burn After Reading
Description: A disk containing mysterious information from a CIA agent ends up in the hands of two unscrupulous and daft gym employees who attempt to sell it.

Title: 1556. Love Actually
Description: Follows the lives of eight very different couples in dealing with their love lives in various loosely interrelated tales all set during a frantic month before Christmas in London, England.

Title: 1557. Scrooged
Description: A selfish, cynical television executive is haunted by three spirits bearing lessons on Christmas Eve.

Title: 1558. Why Him?
Description: A holiday gathering threatens to go off the rails when Ned Fleming realizes that his daughter's Silicon Valley millionaire boyfriend is about to pop the question.

Title: 1559. Blockers
Description: Three parents try to stop their daughters from losing their virginity on prom night.

Title: 1560. The King of Kings
Description: Through a father's vivid storytelling, a boy journeys through Jesus' life, from humble beginnings to ultimate sacrifice. Along the way, he discovers the transformative power of faith.

Title: 1561. The Cable Guy
Description: A designer makes a grievous mistake when he rejects the friendship of a borderline cable guy.

Title: 1562. Resident Evil: Afterlife
Description: While still out to destroy the evil Umbrella Corporation, Alice joins a group of survivors living in a prison surrounded by the infected who also want to relocate to the mysterious but supposedly unharmed safe haven known only as Arcadia.

Title: 1563. Spies Like Us
Description: Two bumbling government employees think they are U.S. spies, only to discover that they are actually decoys for Nuclear War.

Title: 1564. Why Did I Get Married Too?
Description: Four couples struggle to save their marriages once again on their annual marriage retreat, while each of them battle through financial, physical, mental, and emotional issues.

Title: 1565. The American President
Description: A widowed U.S. President running for reelection and an environmental lobbyist fall in love. It's all above-board, but "politics is perception," and sparks fly anyway.

Title: 1566. Species
Description: A group of scientists try to track down and trap a killer alien seductress before she successfully mates with a human.

Title: 1567. The Family Stone
Description: An uptight businesswoman accompanies her boyfriend to his eccentric and outgoing family's annual Christmas celebration and finds that she's a fish out of water in their free-spirited way of life.

Title: 1568. Bad Santa
Description: A miserable conman and his partner pose as Santa and his Little Helper to rob department stores on Christmas Eve. But they run into problems when the conman befriends a troubled kid.

Title: 1569. Brüno
Description: Flamboyant, gay Austrian Brüno looks for new fame in America.

Title: 1570. Hope Floats
Description: Birdee Calvert must choose between her morals and her heart after her husband divorces her and a charming young man, who her daughter disapproves of, comes back into her life.

Title: 1571. Tooth Fairy
Description: A bad deed on the part of a tough minor-league hockey player results in an unusual sentence: He must serve one week as a real-life tooth fairy.

Title: 1572. Snow Day
Description: When a school in upstate New York is snowed in, a group of students hi-jack a plow to keep the school closed.

Title: 1573. The Good Shepherd
Description: The tumultuous early history of the Central Intelligence Agency is viewed through the prism of one man's life.

Title: 1574. Superman III
Description: Entrepreneur Ross Webster teams up with a computer genius in order to realise his own evil intentions. When Superman obstructs his plans, he decides to destroy him.

Title: 1575. Jungle 2 Jungle
Description: A man learns he has a thirteen-year-old son who was raised in the jungle and brings the boy to New York City, turning his life upside down in the process.

Title: 1576. Little Miss Sunshine
Description: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

Title: 1577. Pacific Rim: Uprising
Description: Jake Pentecost, son of Stacker Pentecost, reunites with Mako Mori to lead a new generation of Jaeger pilots, including rival Lambert and 15-year-old hacker Amara, against a new Kaiju threat.

Title: 1578. The Benchwarmers
Description: A trio of guys try and make up for missed opportunities in childhood by forming a three-player baseball team to compete against standard children's Little League squads.

Title: 1579. Predator
Description: A team of commandos on a mission in a Central American jungle find themselves hunted by an extraterrestrial warrior.

Title: 1580. Secretariat
Description: Penny Chenery Tweedy and colleagues guide her long-shot but precocious stallion to set, in 1973, the unbeaten record for winning the Triple Crown.

Title: 1581. Son of God
Description: The life story of Jesus is told from his humble birth through his teachings, crucifixion and ultimate resurrection.

Title: 1582. Gothika
Description: A psychiatrist awakens as a patient in a mental institution, with no memory of the murder she's accused of committing. As she tries to regain her memory, a vengeful spirit manipulates her.

Title: 1583. My Big Fat Greek Wedding 2
Description: A Portokalos family secret brings the beloved characters back together for an even bigger and Greeker wedding.

Title: 1584. The Dictator
Description: The heroic story of a dictator who risked his life to ensure that democracy would never come to the country he so lovingly oppressed.

Title: 1585. Hellboy
Description: A demon raised from infancy after being conjured by and rescued from the Nazis, grows up to become a defender against the forces of darkness.

Title: 1586. The Last Boy Scout
Description: A private detective's protected female witness is murdered, prompting him and the victim's boyfriend to investigate the crime that leads to a corrupt politician and a crooked football team owner.

Title: 1587. My Girl
Description: Vada is obsessed with death. Her mother is dead, and her father runs a funeral parlor. When Vada's father hires Shelly, a makeup expert, and begins to fall in love, Vada is outraged and does everything in her power to split them up.

Title: 1588. The Stepford Wives
Description: The secret to a Stepford wife lies behind the doors of the Men's Association.

Title: 1589. The Lego Ninjago Movie
Description: Shunned by everyone for being the son of an evil warlord, a teenager seeks to defeat him with the help of his fellow ninjas.

Title: 1590. The Grand Budapest Hotel
Description: A writer encounters the owner of an aging high-class hotel, who tells him of his early years serving as a lobby boy in the hotel's glorious years under an exceptional concierge.

Title: 1591. Planes: Fire & Rescue
Description: When Dusty learns that his engine is damaged and he may never race again, he joins a forest fire and rescue unit to be trained as a firefighter, or else his air strip will be shut down.

Title: 1592. Transformers One
Description: The untold origin story of Optimus Prime and Megatron, better known as sworn enemies, but who once were friends bonded like brothers who changed the fate of Cybertron forever.

Title: 1593. Courage Under Fire
Description: A U.S. Army officer, despondent about a deadly mistake he made, investigates a female chopper commander's worthiness for the Medal of Honor.

Title: 1594. Dawn of the Dead
Description: A nurse, a policeman, a young married couple and other survivors of a worldwide plague that is producing aggressive, flesh-eating zombies take refuge in a mega Midwestern shopping mall.

Title: 1595. The Aristocats
Description: With the help of a smooth talking tomcat, a family of Parisian felines set to inherit a fortune from their owner try to make it back home after a jealous butler kidnaps them and leaves them in the country.

Title: 1596. Chariots of Fire
Description: Two British track athletes, one a determined Jew and the other a devout Christian, are driven to win in the 1924 Olympics as they wrestle with issues of pride and conscience.

Title: 1597. Vacation
Description: Rusty Griswold takes his own family on a road trip to "Walley World" in order to spice things up with his wife and reconnect with his sons.

Title: 1598. Far and Away
Description: A young Irish couple flee to the States, but subsequently struggle to obtain land and prosper freely.

Title: 1599. Total Recall
Description: A factory worker, Douglas Quaid, begins to suspect that he is a spy after visiting Rekall - a company that provides its clients with implanted fake memories of a life they would like to have led - goes wrong and he finds himself on the run.

Title: 1600. Surf's Up
Description: A behind-the-scenes look at the annual Penguin World Surfing Championship, and its newest participant, up-and-comer Cody Maverick.

Title: 1601. Behind Enemy Lines
Description: A disillusioned navigator, shot down over war-torn Bosnia, goes on the run from the local military as well as an assassin, while his commanding officer risks all to save him.

Title: 1602. The Blue Lagoon
Description: During the Victorian period, two preteen cousins are shipwrecked on a tropical island in the South Pacific and enjoy a simple life together until puberty complicates matters.

Title: 1603. Bride Wars
Description: Two best friends become rivals when their weddings end up scheduled on the same day.

Title: 1604. Water for Elephants
Description: Jacob takes a job as an animal caretaker in a traveling circus. There he meets Marlena, a beautiful circus performer. Their shared compassion for a special elephant Rosie leads to love, but Marlena's cruel husband stands in their way.

Title: 1605. Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
Description: Jack Reacher must uncover the truth behind a major government conspiracy in order to clear his name while on the run as a fugitive from the law.

Title: 1606. Honey, I Blew Up the Kid
Description: The Szalinski family is back, this time hilarious disaster strikes when an experiment causes their new toddler son to grow many stories tall.

Title: 1607. Little Man
Description: A wannabe-dad mistakes a vertically-challenged criminal on the lam for his newly-adopted son.

Title: 1608. Jack
Description: Because of an unusual disorder that has aged him four times faster than a typical human being, a boy looks like a 40-year-old man as he starts fifth grade at public school after being homeschooled.

Title: 1609. RoboCop
Description: In 2028 Detroit, when Alex Murphy, a loving husband, father and good cop, is critically injured in the line of duty, the multinational conglomerate OmniCorp sees their chance for a part-man, part-robot police officer.

Title: 1610. Sea of Love
Description: A detective investigating a series of murders becomes involved with a woman who may be the culprit.

Title: 1611. The Croods: A New Age
Description: The prehistoric family the Croods are challenged by a rival family the Bettermans, who claim to be better and more evolved.

Title: 1612. Tenet
Description: Armed with only the word "Tenet," and fighting for the survival of the entire world, CIA operative, The Protagonist, journeys through a twilight world of international espionage on a global mission that unfolds beyond real time.

Title: 1613. HouseSitter
Description: Con artist Gwen moves into Newton's empty home without his knowledge and begins setting up house, posing as his new wife.

Title: 1614. Death Becomes Her
Description: When a fading actress learns of an immortality treatment, she sees it as a way to outdo her long-time rival.

Title: 1615. Anastasia
Description: The last surviving child of the Russian Royal Family joins two con men to reunite with her grandmother, the Dowager Empress, while the undead Rasputin seeks her death.

Title: 1616. Easy A
Description: When Olive lies to her best friend about losing her virginity to one of the college boys, a girl overhears their conversation. Soon, her story spreads across the entire school like wildfire.

Title: 1617. Curious George
Description: The Man in the Yellow Hat is an oddball museum employee who looks after his pet monkey, an inquisitive and wonderful creature whose enthusiasm often gets the best of him.

Title: 1618. Open Range
Description: A former gunslinger is forced to take up arms again when he and his cattle crew are threatened by a corrupt landowner.

Title: 1619. Joker: Folie à Deux
Description: Struggling with his dual identity, failed comedian Arthur Fleck meets the love of his life, Harley Quinn, while incarcerated at Arkham State Hospital.

Title: 1620. Halloween
Description: After being committed for 15 years, Michael Myers, now a grown man and still very dangerous, escapes from the mental institution and immediately returns to Haddonfield to find his baby sister, Laurie.

Title: 1621. Tomb Raider
Description: Lara Croft, the fiercely independent daughter of a missing adventurer, must push herself beyond her limits when she discovers the island where her father, Lord Richard Croft disappeared.

Title: 1622. The Secret Life of Walter Mitty
Description: When both he and a colleague are about to lose their job, Walter takes action by embarking on an adventure more extraordinary than anything he ever imagined.

Title: 1623. Bicentennial Man
Description: The life and times of Andrew, a robot purchased as a household appliance programmed to perform menial tasks. As Andrew begins to experience emotions and creative thought, the Martin family soon discovers they don't have an ordinary robot.

Title: 1624. Ali
Description: A biography of sports legend Muhammad Ali, focusing on his triumphs and controversies between 1964 and 1974.

Title: 1625. Without a Paddle
Description: After their friend dies, three men decide to fulfill their childhood dream by going on a camping expedition for the lost D. B. Cooper bounty, with calamitous results.

Title: 1626. Baywatch
Description: Devoted lifeguard Mitch Buchannon butts heads with a brash new recruit, as they uncover a criminal plot that threatens the future of the bay.

Title: 1627. Demolition Man
Description: A police officer is brought out of suspended animation in prison to pursue an old ultra-violent nemesis who is loose in a non-violent future society.

Title: 1628. Ballerina
Description: An assassin trained in the traditions of the Ruska Roma organization sets out to seek revenge after her father's death.

Title: 1629. Maze Runner: The Death Cure
Description: Young hero Thomas embarks on a mission to find a cure for a deadly disease known as "The Flare".

Title: 1630. Step Up 2 the Streets
Description: Romantic sparks occur between two dance students from different backgrounds at the Maryland School of the Arts.

Title: 1631. The Lincoln Lawyer
Description: Defence lawyer Mick Haller lands a case defending a wealthy realtor's son who is accused of raping a prostitute. Believing his client to be innocent, Haller soon finds evidence that proves otherwise.

Title: 1632. The Butterfly Effect
Description: Evan Treborn suffers blackouts during significant events of his life. As he grows up, he finds a way to remember these lost memories and a supernatural way to alter his life by reading his journal.

Title: 1633. Throw Momma from the Train
Description: A bitter writing teacher wants his successful ex-wife dead. A put-upon mama's boy writing student wants his overbearing mother dead. Will there be a criss-cross murder plot?

Title: 1634. Red Eye
Description: Lisa on her flight to Miami befriends Jackson who turns out to be a terrorist. Holding her hostage, he forces her to help him assassinate the United States Deputy Secretary of Homeland Security.

Title: 1635. Shall We Dance?
Description: A romantic comedy where a bored, overworked Estate Lawyer, upon first sight of a beautiful instructor, signs up for ballroom dancing lessons.

Title: 1636. Invincible
Description: Based on the story of Vince Papale, a 30-year-old bartender from South Philadelphia who overcame long odds to play for the NFL's Philadelphia Eagles in 1976.

Title: 1637. Cleopatra
Description: Queen Cleopatra VII of Egypt experiences both triumph and tragedy as she attempts to resist the imperial ambitions of Rome.

Title: 1638. The Chronicles of Riddick
Description: The wanted criminal Richard Bruno Riddick arrives on a planet called Helion Prime and finds himself up against an invading empire called the Necromongers, an army that plans to convert or kill all humans in the universe.

Title: 1639. Takers
Description: A group of bank robbers find their multi-million dollar plan interrupted by a hard-boiled detective.

Title: 1640. Jackass Forever
Description: After 11 years, the Jackass crew is back for another crusade.

Title: 1641. The Animal
Description: After receiving organ transplants from various animal donors, a man finds himself taking on the traits of those animals.

Title: 1642. Fences
Description: A working-class African-American father tries to raise his family in the 1950s, while coming to terms with the events of his life.

Title: 1643. Shazam! Fury of the Gods
Description: The film continues the story of teenage Billy Batson who, upon reciting the magic word "SHAZAM!", is transformed into his adult superhero alter ego, Shazam.

Title: 1644. Life Is Beautiful
Description: When an open-minded Jewish waiter and his son become victims of the Holocaust, he uses a perfect mixture of will, humor and imagination to protect his son from the dangers around their camp.

Title: 1645. The Cider House Rules
Description: During World War II, an orphan grows up under the tutelage of a doctor who runs an orphanage. However, he yearns for freedom and soon decides to leave in order to make a life for himself.

Title: 1646. Boyz n the Hood
Description: Follows the lives of three young males living in the Crenshaw ghetto of Los Angeles, dissecting questions of race, relationships, violence, and future prospects.

Title: 1647. Memoirs of a Geisha
Description: The heartwarming tale of Nitta Sayuri, a young Japanese woman who transcended from her fishing-village roots and became one of Japan's most celebrated geisha.

Title: 1648. Pet Sematary
Description: After tragedy strikes, a grieving father discovers an ancient burial ground behind his home with the power to raise the dead.

Title: 1649. Dragnet
Description: The equally strait-laced and "by-the-book" nephew of Joe Friday must work with his more laid-back partner to solve a mystery.

Title: 1650. Moulin Rouge!
Description: A poor Bohemian poet in 1890s Paris falls for a beautiful courtesan and nightclub star coveted by a jealous duke.

Title: 1651. The Shack
Description: A grieving man receives a mysterious, personal invitation to meet with God at a place called "The Shack."

Title: 1652. Blood Diamond
Description: A fisherman, a smuggler, and a syndicate of businessmen match wits over the possession of a priceless diamond.

Title: 1653. The Specialist
Description: A woman entices a bomb expert she's involved with into destroying the mafia that killed her family.

Title: 1654. Next Friday

Title: 1655. Sister Act 2: Back in the Habit

Title: 1656. The Boss Baby: Family Business
Description: The Templeton brothers have become adults and drifted away from each other, but a new boss baby with a cutting-edge approach is about to bring them together again - and inspire a new family business.

Title: 1657. Willow
Description: A young dwarf farmer is chosen to undertake a perilous journey in order to protect a special baby from an evil queen. Along the way, he teams up with a disgraced swordsman to defeat the evil sorceress.

Title: 1658. The Whole Nine Yards

Title: 1659. 13 Going on 30
Description: Unpopular schoolgirl Jenna Rink makes an unusual wish on her birthday. Miraculously, her wish comes true and the 13-year-old Jenna wakes up the next day as a 30-year-old woman.

Title: 1660. The Blues Brothers

Description: U.S. Marshal Samuel Gerard and his team of Marshals are assigned to track down Sheridan, who has been accused of a double-murder.

Title: 1662. Godzilla Minus One
Description: A kamikaze pilot plagued by survivor's guilt seeks redemption when a giant monster he failed to kill is transformed by radiation from atomic bomb tests and lays siege to post-war Japan.

Title: 1663. 12 Monkeys
Description: In a future world devastated by disease, a convict is sent back in time to gather information about the man-made virus that wiped out most of the human population on the planet.

Title: 1664. Unlawful Entry
Description: A burglar holds a knife to Karen's throat while her husband does nothing. The couple ends up befriending the cop that comes. The friendship ends when the cop beats up the culprit. Karen isn't ready to end it. Things get ugly with the cop.

Title: 1665. Beethoven
Description: A slobbering St. Bernard becomes the center of attention for George and Alice Newton's loving family, who must contend with dog-napping local veterinarian Dr. Herman Varnick and his henchmen Harvey and Vernon.

Title: 1666. Annie
Description: A spunky young orphan is taken in by a rich eccentric, much to the chagrin of the cantankerous woman who runs the orphanage.

Title: 1667. Beaches
Description: Wealthy privileged San Francisco debutante Hillary Whitney Essex and cynical struggling entertainer C. C. Bloom share a turbulent, but strong friendship over the years.

Title: 1668. The Perfect Guy
Description: After breaking up with her boyfriend, a professional woman gets involved with a man who seems almost too good to be true.

Title: 1669. Escape from Planet Earth
Description: Astronaut Scorch Supernova finds himself caught in a trap when he responds to an SOS from a notoriously dangerous alien planet, Earth.

Title: 1670. American Reunion
Description: Jim, Michelle, Stifler, and their friends reunite in East Great Falls, Michigan for their high school reunion.

Title: 1671. Escape Room
Description: Six strangers find themselves in a maze of deadly mystery rooms and must use their wits to survive.

Title: 1672. The Man in the Iron Mask
Description: The cruel King Louis XIV of France has a secret twin brother whom he keeps imprisoned. Can the twin be substituted for the real king?

Title: 1673. Shanghai Noon
Description: A Chinese man travels to the Wild West to rescue a kidnapped Princess. After teaming up with a train robber, the unlikely duo takes on a Chinese traitor and his corrupt boss.

Title: 1674. Midway

Description: Hoping to alter the events of the past, a 19th century inventor instead travels 800,000 years into the future, where he finds humankind divided into two warring races.

Title: 1676. Midnight in Paris
Description: While on a trip to Paris with his fiancée's family, a nostalgic screenwriter finds himself mysteriously going back to the 1920s every day at midnight.

Title: 1679. 12 Years a Slave

Title: 1680. Guess Who's Coming to Dinner

Description: Shallow, rich and socially successful Cher is at the top of her Beverly Hills high school's pecking scale. Seeing herself as a matchmaker, Cher first coaxes two teachers into dating each other.

Title: 1682. Rat Race

Title: 1683. A Knight's Tale
Description: After his master dies, a peasant squire, fueled by his desire for food and glory, creates a new identity for himself as a knight.

Title: 1684. Executive Decision
Description: When terrorists seize control of an airliner, an intelligence analyst accompanies a commando unit for a midair boarding operation.

Description: A successful lawman's plans to retire anonymously in Tombstone, Arizona, are disrupted by the kind of outlaws he was famous for eliminating.

Title: 1687. Darkest Hour

Title: 1688. Joy

Title: 1689. The Queen
Description: After the death of Princess Diana, Queen Elizabeth II struggles with her reaction to a sequence of events nobody could have predicted.

Title: 1690. The Big Chill
Description: A group of seven former college friends gather for a weekend reunion at a South Carolina vacation home after the funeral of another of their college friends.

Title: 1691. Drumline
Description: A band director recruits a Harlem street drummer to play at a Southern university.

Title: 1692. White Noise
Description: An architect's desire to speak with his wife from beyond the grave becomes an obsession with supernatural repercussions.

Description: The solitary life of an artificial man - who was incompletely constructed and has scissors for hands - is upended when he is taken in by a suburban family.

Title: 1694. Once Upon a Time in Mexico

Description: As his kingdom is being threatened by the Turks, young prince Vlad Tepes must become a monster feared by his own people in order to obtain the power needed to protect his own family, and the families of his kingdom.

Title: 1696. Me Before You
Description: A girl in a small town forms an unlikely bond with a recently-paralyzed man she's taking care of.

Title: 1697. Just Married
Description: A young newlywed couple honeymoon in Europe, where obstacles challenge their ability to sustain the marriage.

Title: 1698. Fantastic Four
Description: Four young outsiders teleport to an alternate and dangerous universe which alters their physical form in shocking ways. The four must learn to harness their new abilities and work together to save Earth from a former friend turned enemy.

Title: 1699. Primal Fear
Description: A high-profile murder intrigues a publicity hungry lawyer.

Title: 1700. Wallace & Gromit: The Curse of the Were-Rabbit
Description: Wallace and his loyal dog, Gromit, set out to discover the mystery behind the garden sabotage that plagues their village and threatens the annual giant vegetable growing contest.

Title: 1701. Be Cool
Description: Disenchanted with the movie industry, Chili Palmer tries the music industry, meeting and romancing a widow of a music executive on the way.

Title: 1702. ParaNorman
Description: A misunderstood boy takes on ghosts, zombies and grown-ups to save his town from a centuries-old curse.

Title: 1703. Saw
Description: Two men awaken to find themselves on the opposite sides of a dead body, each with specific instructions to kill the other, escape or face the consequences. These two are the latest contestants in Jigsaw's games.

Title: 1704. Romeo Must Die
Description: An avenging cop seeks out his brother's killer and falls for the daughter of a businessman who is involved in a money-deal with his father.

Title: 1705. Forever Young
Description: During a cryogenics test, a pilot frozen in 1939 awakes in 1992 but time is running out, as his body starts to age rapidly.

Title: 1706. The Suicide Squad

Title: 1707. Friends with Benefits
Description: A young man and woman decide to take their friendship to the next level without becoming a couple, but soon discover that adding sex only leads to complications.

Title: 1708. Free Birds
Description: A pair of turkeys discover a time machine and decide to use it to travel to the first Thanksgiving, to take turkeys off the menu forever.

Title: 1709. Hansel & Gretel: Witch Hunters
Description: Brother/sister duo Hansel and Gretel are professional witch-hunters who help innocent villagers. One day they stumble upon a case that could hold the key to their past.

Title: 1710. Eyes Wide Shut
Description: A Manhattan doctor embarks on a bizarre, night-long odyssey after his wife's admission of unfulfilled longing.

Title: 1711. Happy Death Day

Title: 1714. Snake Eyes
Description: Corrupt Atlantic City police officer Rick Santoro and Navy Commander Kevin Dunn join forces to investigate both the assassination of Secretary of Defense Charles Kirkland and the disappearance of a beautiful stranger.

Title: 1715. The BFG
Description: An orphan little girl befriends a benevolent giant who takes her to Giant Country, where they attempt to stop the man-eating giants that are invading the human world.

Title: 1716. Never Been Kissed
Description: A newspaper reporter enrolls in high school as part of research for a story.

Title: 1717. Alien³

Title: 1719. Never Say Never Again

Title: 1720. The Haunting in Connecticut
Description: After a family is forced to relocate for their son's health, they begin experiencing supernatural behavior in their new home, and uncover a sinister history.

Title: 1721. What Dreams May Come

Title: 1722. Ghosts of Girlfriends Past

Title: 1723. Why Did I Get Married?
Description: The big-screen adaptation of Perry's stage play about the trials of marriage and what happens to one family when a sexy young temptress arrives on the scene.

Title: 1724. The Shallows
Description: A mere 200 yards from shore, surfer Nancy is attacked by a great white shark, with her short journey to safety becoming the ultimate contest of wills.

Title: 1725. I Am Number Four

Title: 1726. Halloween H20: 20 Years Later

Title: 1728. Don't Say a Word
Description: When the daughter of a psychiatrist is kidnapped, he's horrified to discover that the abductors' demand is that he break through to a post traumatic stress disorder suffering young woman who knows a secret...

Title: 1729. The Abyss
Description: A civilian diving team is enlisted to search for a lost nuclear submarine and faces danger while encountering an alien aquatic species.

Title: 1730. The Jackal
Description: An imprisoned I.R.A. fighter is freed to help stop a brutal, seemingly "faceless" assassin from completing his next job.

Title: 1731. Spawn
Description: An elite mercenary is killed, but comes back from Hell as a reluctant soldier of the Devil.

Title: 1732. The Nutcracker and the Four Realms
Description: A young girl is transported into a magical world of gingerbread soldiers and an army of mice.

Title: 1733. Doc Hollywood
Description: A young doctor on his way across the country to a job interview crashes his car in a small town and is sentenced to work for several days at the town hospital.

Title: 1734. Starship Troopers
Description: Humans, in a fascist militaristic future, wage war with giant alien bugs.

Title: 1735. For Your Eyes Only
Description: Secret service agent James Bond is assigned to find a missing British vessel equipped with a weapons encryption device and prevent it from falling into enemy hands.

Title: 1736. Office Christmas Party
Description: When his uptight CEO sister threatens to shut down his branch, the branch manager throws an epic Christmas party in order to land a big client and save the day, but the party gets way out of hand...

Title: 1737. Ordinary People
Description: The accidental death of the older son of an affluent family deeply strains the relationships among the bitter mother, the good-natured father and the guilt-ridden younger son.

Title: 1738. This Means War
Description: CIA agents and best friends Franklin and Tuck discover that they are in love with the same woman. Each of them then decides to win her over by using their own skills.

Title: 1739. The Curse of La Llorona
Description: Ignoring the eerie warning of a troubled mother suspected of child endangerment, a social worker and her own small kids are soon drawn into a frightening supernatural realm.

Title: 1740. Project X
Description: Three high-school seniors throw a birthday party to make a name for themselves. As the night progresses, things spiral out of control as word of the party spreads.

Title: 1741. Tag
Description: A small group of former classmates organize an elaborate, annual game of tag that requires some to travel all over the country.

Title: 1742. Pet Sematary
Description: Dr. Louis Creed and his wife, Rachel, relocate from Boston to rural Maine with their two young children. The couple soon discover a mysterious burial ground hidden deep in the woods near their new home.

Title: 1743. Raya and the Last Dragon

Title: 1744. Source Code
Description: A soldier wakes up in someone else's body and discovers he's part of an experimental government program to find the bomber of a commuter train within 8 minutes.

Title: 1745. Small Soldiers
Description: When missile technology is used to enhance toy action figures, the toys soon begin to take their battle programming too seriously.

Title: 1746. Assassin's Creed
Description: Callum Lynch explores the memories of his ancestor Aguilar de Nerha and gains the skills of a Master Assassin, before taking on the secret Templar society.

Title: 1747. What Men Want
Description: A woman is boxed out by the male sports agents in her profession, but gains an unexpected edge over them when she develops the ability to hear men's thoughts.

Title: 1748. The Omen
Description: An American official realizes that his young son may literally be the Devil incarnate.

Title: 1749. Crash
Description: Racial tensions collide in a collection of intertwined stories involving residents of Los Angeles.

Title: 1750. New Year's Eve
Description: The lives of several couples and singles in New York City intertwine over the course of New Year's Eve.

Title: 1751. Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri
Description: A mother personally challenges the local authorities to solve her daughter's murder when they fail to catch the culprit.

Title: 1752. Horrible Bosses 2
Description: Dale, Kurt and Nick decide to start their own business but things don't go as planned because of a slick investor, prompting the trio to pull off a harebrained and misguided kidnapping scheme.

Title: 1753. The Woman in Black
Description: A young solicitor travels to a remote village where he discovers that the vengeful ghost of a scorned woman is terrorizing the locals.

Title: 1754. The Hundred-Foot Journey
Description: The Kadam family leaves India for France where they open a restaurant directly across the road from Madame Mallory's Michelin-starred eatery.

Title: 1755. Evil Dead
Description: Five friends head to a remote cabin, where the discovery of a Book of the Dead leads them to unwittingly summon up demons living in the nearby woods.

Title: 1756. The Count of Monte Cristo
Description: A young man, falsely imprisoned by his jealous "friend", escapes and uses a hidden treasure to exact his revenge.

Title: 1757. La Bamba
Description: Biographical story of the rise from nowhere of early rock and roll singer Ritchie Valens who died at age 17 in a plane crash with Buddy Holly and The Big Bopper.

Title: 1758. TMNT
Description: When the world is threatened by an ancient evil, the Ninja Turtles must reunite and overcome their faults in order to stand against it.

Title: 1759. The Hateful Eight
Description: In the dead of a Wyoming winter, a bounty hunter and his prisoner find shelter in a cabin currently inhabited by a collection of nefarious characters.

Title: 1760. Final Destination 3
Description: Wendy Christensen and a group of teens who escaped a fatal roller-coaster crash face a bloody date with Death.

Title: 1761. Barbershop: The Next Cut
Description: As their surrounding community has taken a turn for the worse, the crew at Calvin's Barbershop come together to bring some much needed change to their neighborhood.

Title: 1762. Insidious
Description: A family looks to prevent evil spirits from trapping their comatose child in a realm called The Further.

Title: 1763. Terrifier 3
Description: Art the Clown is set to unleash chaos on the unsuspecting residents of Miles County as they peacefully drift off to sleep on Christmas Eve.

Title: 1764. The Verdict
Description: An alcoholic Boston lawyer fights a law firm dean.

Title: 1765. Austin Powers: International Man of Mystery
Description: A world-class playboy and part-time secret agent from the 1960s emerges after thirty years in a cryogenic state to battle with his nemesis Dr. Evil.

Title: 1767. Paranormal Activity 4
Description: It has been five years since the disappearance of Katie and Hunter, and a suburban family witness strange events in their neighborhood when a woman and a mysterious child move in.

Title: 1768. Focus
Description: In the midst of veteran con man Nicky's latest scheme, a woman from his past - now an accomplished femme fatale - shows up and throws his plans for a loop.

Title: 1769. Tin Cup
Description: A washed-up golf pro working at a driving range tries to qualify for the U.S. Open in order to win the heart of his successful rival's girlfriend.

Title: 1770. Parasite
Description: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

Title: 1771. House of Gucci
Description: When Patrizia Reggiani, an outsider from humble beginnings, marries into the Gucci family, her unbridled ambition begins to unravel their legacy and triggers a reckless spiral of betrayal, decadence, revenge, and ultimately...murder.

Title: 1772. Paycheck
Description: A technical wizard learns that his memory has been erased.

Title: 1773. Rambo III
Description: Loner Rambo leaves a Buddhist monastery to free his Green Beret mentor from Soviets in Afghanistan.

Title: 1774. Hero
Description: A defense officer, Nameless, was summoned by the King of Qin regarding his success of terminating three warriors.

Title: 1775. P.S. I Love You
Description: A young widow discovers that her late husband has left her 10 messages intended to help ease her pain and start a new life.

Title: 1776. Sabrina
Description: An ugly duckling having undergone a remarkable change, still harbors feelings for her crush: a carefree playboy, but not before his business-focused brother has something to say about it.

Title: 1777. Rookie of the Year
Description: When an accident miraculously gives a boy an incredibly powerful pitching arm, he becomes a major league pitcher for the Chicago Cubs.

Title: 1778. Saw X
Description: A sick and desperate John travels to Mexico for a risky and experimental medical procedure in hopes of a miracle cure for his cancer only to discover the entire operation is a scam to defraud the most vulnerable.

Title: 1779. 3:10 to Yuma
Description: A small-time rancher agrees to hold a captured outlaw who's awaiting a train to go to court in Yuma. A battle of wills ensues as the outlaw tries to psych out the rancher.

Title: 1780. A Simple Favor
Description: Stephanie is a single mother with a parenting vlog who befriends Emily, a secretive upper-class woman who has a child at the same elementary school. When Emily goes missing, Stephanie takes it upon herself to investigate.

Title: 1781. Problem Child
Description: A young boy just short of a monster is adopted by a loving man and his wacky wife. The laughs keep coming as he pushes them to the limits.

Title: 1782. Beethoven's 2nd
Description: Beethoven, the St. Bernard dog, becomes a father, but his girlfriend Missy is dognapped, and his puppies are in danger of the same fate.

Title: 1783. RoboCop
Description: In a violent future in Old Detroit, murdered police officer Alex Murphy is resurrected as RoboCop, a powerful cyborg law enforcer. As he fights crime, he begins to recover memories of his past and seeks revenge on the gang who killed him.

Title: 1784. Yours, Mine & Ours
Description: A widowed Coast Guard Admiral and a widowed handbag designer fall in love and marry, much to the dismay of his 8 and her 10 children.

Title: 1785. Corpse Bride
Description: When a shy groom practices his wedding vows in the inadvertent presence of a deceased young woman, she rises from the grave assuming he has married her.

Title: 1786. Life as We Know It
Description: Two single adults become caregivers to an orphaned girl when their mutual best friends die in an accident.

Title: 1787. T-Rex: Back to the Cretaceous
Description: A youth who finds a dinosaur egg accidentally breaks it. Soon after, she begins to have surreal visions of dinosaurs, including the Tyrannosaurus Rex.

Title: 1788. Madea's Big Happy Family
Description: The crazy and comical Mabel Simmons, otherwise known as Madea, tries to wrangle her fighting family together for a family dinner regarding the health of her niece Shirley.

Title: 1789. Final Destination
Description: After getting a premonition about a plane crash on his school trip, Alex, a student, saves a few of his classmates. However, their situation gets complicated when death starts chasing them.

Title: 1790. Sleepers
Description: A reporter and a District Attorney help childhood friends who killed a sadistic guard.

Title: 1791. Papillon
Description: A French convict in the 1930s befriends a fellow criminal as the two of them begin serving their sentence in the South American penal colony on Devil's Island, which inspires the man to plot his escape.

Title: 1792. RED 2
Description: Retired CIA agent Frank Moses reunites his unlikely team of elite operatives for a global quest to track down a missing portable nuclear device.

Title: 1793. The Devil Inside
Description: In Italy, a woman becomes involved in a series of unauthorized exorcisms during her mission to discover what happened to her mother, who allegedly murdered three people during her own exorcism.

Title: 1794. Arachnophobia
Description: A new species of South American killer spider hitches a lift to a California town in a coffin and starts to breed, leaving a trail of deaths that puzzle and terrify young Dr. Ross Jennings, who is newly arrived in town with his family.

Title: 1795. The Prestige
Description: Rival 19th-century magicians engage in a bitter battle for trade secrets.

Title: 1796. Life of the Party
Description: After her husband abruptly asks for a divorce, a middle-aged mother returns to college in order to complete her degree.

Title: 1797. Letters to Juliet
Description: Sophie travels to Verona where she finds an old unanswered letter asking for love advice. She answers it and when the recipient shows up along with her grumpy grandson, they head off to find the old long lost love while a young love sparks

Title: 1798. Blow
Description: The story of how George Jung, along with the Medellín Cartel headed by Pablo Escobar, established the American cocaine market in the 1970s in the United States.

Title: 1799. My Cousin Vinny
Description: Two New Yorkers accused of murder in rural Alabama while on their way back to college call in the help of one of their cousins, a loudmouth lawyer with no trial experience.

Title: 1800. Forces of Nature
Description: A soon-to-be-married man encounters an exciting stranger after his plane suffers an accident on takeoff.

Title: 1801. Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street
Description: The legendary tale of a barber who returns from wrongful imprisonment to 1840s London, bent on revenge for the rape and death of his wife, and resumes his trade while forming a sinister partnership with his fellow tenant, Mrs. Lovett.

Title: 1802. Varsity Blues
Description: A back-up quarterback is chosen to lead a Texas football team to victory after the star quarterback is injured.

Title: 1803. Message in a Bottle
Description: A woman discovers a tragic love letter in a bottle on a beach, and is determined to track down its author.

Title: 1804. Outrageous Fortune
Description: Two women unknowingly share the same man, but when he disappears, both go out looking for him and enter his surprisingly dangerous life.

Title: 1805. 13 Hours: The Secret Soldiers of Benghazi
Description: During an attack on a U.S. compound in Libya, a security team struggles to make sense out of the chaos.

Title: 1806. Kicking & Screaming
Description: Family man Phil Weston, a lifelong victim of his father's competitive nature, takes on the coaching duties of a kids' soccer team, and soon realizes that he's also taking on his father's dysfunctional way of relating.

Title: 1807. The Recruit
Description: A brilliant young CIA trainee is asked by his mentor to help find a mole in the Agency.

Title: 1808. Unfaithful
Description: A New York suburban couple's marriage goes dangerously awry when the wife indulges in an adulterous fling.

Title: 1809. Gandhi
Description: The life of the lawyer who became the famed leader of the Indian revolts against the British rule through his philosophy of nonviolent protest.

Title: 1810. Four Weddings and a Funeral
Description: Over the course of five social occasions, a committed bachelor must consider the notion that he may have discovered love.

Title: 1811. Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules
Description: Back in middle school after summer vacation, Greg Heffley and his older brother Rodrick must deal with their parents' misguided attempts to have them bond.

Title: 1812. The Naked Gun
Description: Following in his father's footsteps, a detective works to solve a murder case and save his police department from closure.

Title: 1813. The Boys in the Boat
Description: A 1930s-set story centered on the University of Washington's rowing team, from their Depression-era beginnings.

Title: 1814. King Kong
Description: A petroleum exploration expedition comes to an isolated island and encounters a colossal giant gorilla.

Title: 1815. The Strangers
Description: James Hoyt and Kristen McKay visit an isolated vacation home to enjoy some time together. However, they are in for a rude surprise when three masked assailants make their stay a nightmare.

Title: 1816. Karate Kid: Legends
Description: After kung fu prodigy Li Fong relocates to New York City, he attracts unwanted attention from a local karate champion and embarks on a journey to enter the ultimate karate competition with the help of Mr. Han and Daniel LaRusso.

Title: 1817. No Good Deed
Description: An unstable escaped convict terrorizes a woman who is alone with her two children.

Title: 1818. A Madea Christmas
Description: Madea dispenses her unique form of holiday spirit on a rural town when she's coaxed into helping a friend pay her daughter a surprise visit in the country for Christmas.

Title: 1819. Hubble

Title: 1820. Wall Street: Money Never Sleeps
